\title{inverse image}
\date{2024-01-31}
\author{jonmsterling}
\contributor{marcelofiore}
\taxon{definition}
\import{jms-00JB}

\p{Let #{R\colon A\relto B} be a [relation](jms-00I7). The \dem{inverse image} of #{Y\subseteq B} under #{R} is the set #{\inv-img{R}{Y}\subseteq A} defined below:}

##{
 \inv-img{R}{Y} =
 \compr{a\in A}{
  \forall b\in B\punctdot
  a\mathrel{R}b\implies
  b\in Y
 }
}